data.title: Students Services & Clubs
data.meta_description: Guru Nanak College is one of the top College in Chennai and consistently ranked among India's top private College.
data.text:
June 2021

Investor Awareness Program - a Webinar was conducted for the final year Commerce Students with respect to the financial awareness prevailing in the current market trend. The Event was held on 30.6.21 between 4pm to 5pm, the session was handled by Ms. Rekha Ramanathan. She is a BFSI Trainer from United Training Services India.

July 2021

Overseas Education Awareness Program - an Overseas Education Opportunities session was conducted to all the final year students. The session was aimed at for those who want to pursue higher education abroad. The Session was handled by Mr.Kamal Kant, Vice president, Azent Overseas Education Ltd. The event was held on 16.7.21 between 11am to 12 pm virtually.

Adore India Training - the Placement Soft skills Training was conducted for the final year Life Science Students. The Program was primitively aimed at the upcoming placement drives for them. The Training was conducted from 19.7.21 to 27.7.21 virtually. Various Soft skills trainers from Adore Team had handled the session for our Students.

Career Opportunities in UPSC/Civil Services - a Webinar on how the students shall crack the UPSC Exams and Civil Service Exams. The Program was aimed at the students who were planning to appear for the Govt. Exams. The Session was handled by Mr. Ramadesigan Chief Coordinator, Chinmaya Academy of Civil Services and Mr, Raj Sekar, Competitive Exam Trainer Chinmaya Academy of Civil Services. The Event was held virtually on 30.7.21 between 11am to 12pm.

August 2021

Share Markets Intro - A session on How Share Markets Function, the event was supported by Shine Projects Team. The Event was handled by Mr. Venkata Sri Harsha, CEO of Shine Projects. The Event was conducted Virtually on 2.8.21 between 11am to 12pm. The Introduction to Share Market and its nuances was the key subject of discussion.

Networking Basics - A technical session was how computer system are networked and how information pass through various channels effectively was the key discussion. The event was handled by Mr. Madhan Raj, a technical trainer from Sans Cloud Tech. The Event was conducted virtually on 6.8.21 between 11am to 12pm

Adore India Training - the Placement Soft skills Training was conducted for the final year Science Students. The Program was primitively aimed at the upcoming placement drives for them. The Training was conducted from 16.8.21 to 24.8.21 virtually. Various Soft skills trainers from Adore Team had handled the session for our Students.

GTT and Barclays Soft Skills Training - A Training Session organized by GTT Foundation in association with Barclays CSR Training, basically aimed at UG Final Year Students. Mr. Siva Subramanian from GTT Team has handled the session for our Students. Topics like Group Discussion, Body Language, and Corporate Readiness and to name a few were the context of discussion. The training had been conducted virtually between 26.8.21 to 31.8.21 between 2.30pm to 5.30pm

September 2021

Digital Marketing and its Importance - a Webinar session conducted by NIIT Team. The Importance of Digital Marketing and how they play a significant role in today's arena was the complete discussion. The Program was aimed at all students and it had been conducted virtually on 17.9.21 between 3pm to 4pm

Rubicon and Barclays Soft Skills Training - a Training Session Organized by Rubicon Team in association With Barclays CSR Training, basically aimed at PG Final Year Students. Mr. Kumud Lagade was the trainer from Rubicon who had handled the training session for our students. The Event was conducted virtually from 21.9.21 to 30.9.21 between 3pm to 5pm. Topics like Group Discussion, Personal Interview, The Precise Resume Format was the Key content of discussion.

Adore India Training - the Placement Soft skills Training was conducted for the final year Arts Students. The Program was primitively aimed at the upcoming placement drives for them. The Training was conducted from 6.09.21 to 15.09.21 virtually. Various Soft skills trainers from Adore Team had handled the session for our Students.

October 2021

A Virtual Session on Aptitude Learning - Smart Training Solutions team has offered a session on how Aptitude could be cracked. The Session was aimed at all Final year Students. Mr. Manoj Kumar.S Aptitude Trainer from Smart Training Solutions had handled the session for the students. The Shortcut methods and the easy way to solve the aptitude questions was the Key discussion. The Program was aimed at final year keeping their placements in concern. The Event had been held Virtually on 4.10.21 between 10.30 am to 11.30 am

November 2021

Adore India Training - the Placement Soft skills Training was conducted for the final year Commerce Students. The Program was primitively aimed at the upcoming placement drives for them. The Training was conducted from 8.11.21 to 17.11.21 virtually. Various Soft skills trainers from Adore Team had handled the session for our Students.

Advanced Excel Learning Session - a webinar session basically aimed at how one could do the mastery in excel. The Session was aimed at excel learning to the tutees. Mr. Alok Chauhan from Imarticus learning took and handled the session for our students. The Interactive session was conducted Virtually on 23.11.21 between 11am to 12 pm

January- 2022

Career Opportunities in Civil Services - A Webinar was organized in association with ARAM IAS Academy "Career Opportunities in Civil Services", Mr. Manikandan (IAS) Orated the session for the students. He emphasized on how the students shall prepare for the UPSC and CIVIL Services Exam. The Session was organized for UPSC and CIVIL Service Aspirants. The Event was conducted online on 08/01/22 between 3pm to 4pm

Importance of Communication to get a job in Med - The Placement Team of GNC in association with Mirage Film Institute Organized a Virtual Session on "Importance of Communication to get a job in Media", Primitively aimed at B.Sc. (Visual Communication) Students and the session was also extended to the other department students who have greater interest towards the said topic. Mr. Sam Kumar, Founder and Director of Mirage Film Institute were the Orator. The Event was conducted on 28/01/2022 between 2pm to 3.30pm

Febrauary-2022
